modules.description: Provides functions to parse, manipulate, and serialize raw byte sequences, along with operations on variable-length data structures. Works with byte arrays and custom variable containers for low-level data handling. Used to process network packets and binary file formats with precise control over memory layout.

Handles byte-level data through parsing, manipulation, and serialization, supporting variable-length structures and custom containers. Operates on byte arrays and binary formats, enabling precise memory control for tasks like network packet processing. Supports operations such as reading, writing, and transforming binary data with fine-grained control. Examples include extracting fields from binary files, constructing protocol messages, and modifying serialized data structures.

Provides functions to manipulate and inspect raw byte sequences, including slicing, concatenation, and length retrieval. Works with byte arrays and variable-length data structures represented as t and t_variables. Used for low-level data parsing and network protocol handling.

Handles low-level byte manipulation with functions for slicing, concatenating, and inspecting byte sequences. Operates on types t and t_variables, enabling efficient processing of variable-length data structures. Supports tasks like extracting headers from network packets or assembling fragmented data. Examples include parsing binary protocols and constructing custom data formats.

Manages binary data with low-level operations, including parsing, modifying, and serializing byte arrays. Supports variable-length structures and custom containers, enabling precise control over memory and data representation. Tasks like extracting fields from binary files, building protocol messages, and altering serialized formats are directly achievable. Operations include reading, writing, and transforming binary content with fine-grained manipulation.

Handles establishing and managing WebSocket connections for GraphQL queries and subscriptions. It works with WebSocket endpoints, GraphQL operations, and event streams. Used to send real-time data updates from a GraphQL server to an OCaml-based web client.

Provides low-level byte manipulation and binary data handling, offering functions for slicing, concatenating, and inspecting byte sequences. It works with types t and t_variables, enabling precise control over variable-length data structures and binary content. Users can parse binary protocols, extract fields from files, and construct custom message formats. Examples include assembling network packets and modifying serialized data with fine-grained operations.
